parameters:
\SE\SE[2]That was a little...thrilling. \SE[37]My heart skipped a
beat. \SE\SE[2]'Second place'.
\SE[19] (Tch... I guess I can't kill with just this.)

\SE[50]I apologize for intruding, Chairman. \SE[75]It would have
been easier if we could have taken care of that.

\SE[3]So...this commotion was caused by you after all. \SE[36]I
had hoped that the students of our school would be honorable.

\SE[90]... Nobility? Are you kidding me? \SE[19] There is no way
we can remain noble while enjoying the prosperity that comes from
sucking the blood of innocent people.

\SE[27]It was a necessary sacrifice. \!\SE[0]...You should be
able to understand that too.

\SE[39]Just like how humans can only survive by killing others...
We can only build our paradise on top of sacrifices. \SE[0]There
is nothing else beyond that... Happiness is only found there.

\SE[52]Unfortunately, I fell into your trap. \!\SE[3]I had no
choice but to come and take care of it myself.

Hahaha...! I've been underestimated as well. Moreover, to be
given the title of 'second' instead of Lunaroa.

\SE[76]What are you saying, even though you got beaten by that
guy.

\SE[38]That's right... That girl was special. \SE[1]I've seen
many students, but I've never seen such a genius before...
\SE[2]It's inevitable that you would become second.

\SE[3]Have you ever thought about being second? \!\SE[0]You seem
to be burning with a splendid sense of duty but...

\SE\SE[2]It was all because of your weakness. \SE[36]Not being
able to protect your own family name, \SE\SE[2]and even that
anger of yours... It's just being shifted onto the environment.

\SE[52]Yes, you're right. I was only second, and if I had the
power... I could have protected the Lira family.

\SE[50]If I had been the first... I wouldn't have lost my family
or my father. \SE[51]The way I am now, driven by shallow
justice... \SE[2]It's undoubtedly childish and selfish.

\SE[2]...But you know, that doesn't matter. \SE[3] I just have
something I want to prove by defeating all of you.

\SE[72]...To be honest, I didn't really care about the family
name. \SE[79]I was just happy to see my father smile when I got
good grades on tests.

\SE[74]My Lira family is part of the constellation.... \SE[51]My
father named me after the first magnitude star Vega. It made me
happy to feel like I was living up to his expectations. \SE[79]

\SE[2]That's why this is a continuation of that proof. Because
there was a strong person who conveniently strayed from the path
of righteousness. \SE[7]...I decided to defeat that person and
receive praise from my father.

\SE[20]My name is The Shining First Magnitude Star!! The light
bestowed upon me has not yet faded away! \SE[22]For the sake of
my late father's wishes... Become the foundation of my radiance!!
